slides.title: Freedom of Speech and Social Media on Google.co.uk
Central nodes
slides.text: Newsmedia of different types occupy the most central position in the network. They could either be national magazines (e.g. Wired) or online publications specialised in ICTs (e.g. Arstechnica or The Register) or business (e.g. International Business Times)

slides.title: External nodes
slides.text: Academic Journals and Law publications occupy a more external position and are connected among each other
